inn1.comm: pitching on off and angling in, pushed to mid on. free hit time
slower ball on middle and leg, swung away to straight to square leg. Didn't time that well
short of a good length on the off, defended watchfully on the off side
on a good length outside off and swinging in, Chris Gayle gets on the front foot and tries to defend, misses, and is rapped on the pads. The appeal is turned down, he was struck outside the line
on a good length on the off and swinging in, keeps a little low, Gayle gets on the back foot and flicks it to fine leg for a single
full on the off and angling in, defended carefully on the front foot back to the bowler. Tanvir is getting some good late movement here!
pitched on a good length on the off and swinging in, gets on the back foot and works it short of mid wicket for a quick single
short of a good length on the off and swinging away, left alone, good carry to the keeper there!
on a good length on middle and leg, a little bit of late movement towards the off there, tries to defend it on the back foot, gets an inside edge onto his pads
short of a good length on leg stump, worked off his hips wide of mid wicket for a quick single
beaten!!! pitches short of a good length on middle and angling away from the left hander, Gayle gets on the back foot and tries to defend, the ball just leaves him at the last moment
short of a length on leg stump, Gayle gets on the back foot and tries to work it away fine, is struck on the hips, no run there
short of a good length on middle and off, Gayle pulls it away Calypso style wide of mid on for his team's first boundary
full on off and middle, Chattergoon defends with bat close to the pads on the front foot
beaten!!! full outside off and angling away, a teasing line, the batsman prods at it and misses. That was beautifully bowled!
on a good length on middle and swinging in towards leg, gets on the back foot and pushes it wide of mid on for a single
beaten yet again!! pitches full outside the off and leaves Chris Gayle at just the last moment as he tries to defend on the front foot
short of a length outside off and angling in, played to point
defended to the off side
short of a good length outside off and angling away, left alone
on a good length outside off, moving away from the left hander, left alone once again
short of a good length on the off, defended watchfully off the back foot towards extra cover
short outside leg stump, helped on its way to fine leg, the bowler lucky there, the batsman didn't play it fine enough
on a good length outside off, Gayle has nothing to do with it
short of a good length on middle and leg, Gayle tries to work that one away off his pads towards square leg, misses, and is struck high on the pads.
short of a good length on the off and angling in towards middle, defended back to the bowler off the back foot
on a good length on the off stump, defended comfortably on the off side
short and wide outside off, Chattergoon fails to cash in, mistimes it to cover-point
bowled fuller on the off this time, swinging away from the left hander, left alone to the keeper
this one came back in! Bowled full outside the off, Chattergoon goes for an expansive drive through the covers, misses as the ball angles in just a touch to evade his bat
on a good length on the leg stump, tries to glance it down to fine leg, gets a leg bye towards square leg instead
short of a good length on the off and moving away from the left hander, pushed to point off the back foot
short of a good length outside off, played back to the bowler
short of a good length once again on the off, this one held its line, pushed to point
short on leg stump, Chattergoon tries to play it off his hips towards fine leg, gets a leg bye
swung away for a big one!!! That was pitched short of a length on leg stump, Gayle took a couple of steps down the pitch and pulled it over the mid wicket boundary for a big six!! That was coming!!
full on leg stump and swinging towards middle, Gayle stays his ground and flicks it beautifully over mid on for a boundary. Just a flick of the wrists there and the ball flew away!
short of a good length outside off, leaving the left hander, pushes it at but is beaten
on a good length on middle and leg, defended on the leg side
teasing line, fuller outside the off and angling away from the left hander, left alone this time
on a good length outside leg stump, glanced down to fine leg
pitches short of a good length on middle and leg, Gayle walks across and tries to flick it away wide of square leg, is rapped on the pads, but that was missing leg stump
short of a good length outside off, defended to point off the back foot
short of a length on leg stump, Gayle cashes in, he gets on the back foot and pulls that over mid wicket for a boundary. The Windies getting a move-on now.
that was fuller on the pads, Gayle stays in his crease and flicks that wide of the short-fine leg fielder for another boundary
slower ball bowled from round the wicket on middle and off, full in length, defended back to the bowler

full outside off yet again, not quite a length ball though, but it makes no difference to Gayle and he plants the front foot forward and smashes it over the bowlers head for a boundary. Rauf struggling here! Gayle batting like a millionaire, and I wasn't being figurative there!!
this one goes for four too!! slower ball outside off, Gayle waits for it and guides it beautifully wide of short-third man for the fourth boundary of the over
short of a good length on middle, pushed off the back foot wide of mid wicket for a single
full outside the off, steered to point
fuller outside off and swinging away, Gayle reaches for it and steers it wide of point this time for his seventh boundary
short of a length on the off, struck powerfully, but straight to short-extra cover
short of a length outside off, chopped down to point. Gayle would be disappointed here!
short of a good length outside off, driven firmly off the back foot to mid off
on a good length on off and middle, angling in, Gayle pushes it wide of mid wicket on the front foot and keeps the strike!
short of a length on middle and off, pushed to short extra cover
bouncer!! pitches short on middle, was a touch too high, Gayle backs out. Rightly given a no-ball, for height

big one!!! That was a rank long hop on middle stump, Gayle rocks back on the back foot and pulls it well over square leg for his second six!! That was dispatched to the deep square leg boundary with absolute disdain!!
this is excellent batting!! bowled back of a length from round the wicket on middle stump, Gayle whips it away Calypso style over square leg yet again for another big one!!
short of a length outside off, swatted on the bounce to mid off

pitched short of a good length outside off, Gayle thinks of swatting it back over the bowlers head, but checks his shot at the last moment just when he realises the line isn't right, played back to the bowler
slower ball outside off, Gayle restrains himself and pushes that one to short extra-cover with a bit of difficulty
short of a good length outside off, Chattergoon goes for an ambitious drive, the ball leaves him at just the last moment, and is beaten
connects well this time!! full ball outside off, swinging away, driven on the up, over mid off for his first boundary
short of a good length on the off stump, pushed to point
full outside off, Chattergoon gets on the front foot and slices it wide of third man for a one bounce four. Chattergoon among the runs now!
short of a length on the off and angling in, defended watchfully on the back foot
a bouncer pitched in line on middle and leg, tries to hook it wide fine leg, misses
pitches short of a good length outside off Gayle looks to play it towards the covers, gets an inside edge onto his pads
on a good length on the off this time, played back to the bowler
full ball on middle and leg, flicked away towards fine-leg who's standing a little square, for a couple. Fifty for Gayle!!! 46 runs off his last 24 balls, his 38th fifty in ODIs
back of a length from round the wicket on the off, pushed off the back foot towards mid off
on a good length on the off stump, Chattergoon punches it to cover
short of a length on the off, attempts to pull it over mid wicket, does not connect well, gets a top-edge that falls well out of reach of square-leg. Two runs taken!!
back of a length again on the off stump, tries to pull it wide of mid on, fails to time it well
slower ball outside the off, Gayle gets on the back foot and slaps it down to mid off, again not timed as well as he would have liked
full on off and middle, Gayle stays his ground and with a flick of the wrists, lofts it towards the deep mid wicket boundary for a four. That fell just inside the ropes
short of a length outside off, Gayle swats it down to mid off, who standing a lot straighter, and right on the edge of the circle
fuller on middle and leg, defended watchfully
slower ball on middle and leg, turned to short-fine leg
short outside the off, guided down to third man for a single.
slower ball on middle and off, Gayle goes for a mighty hit down the ground, gets the elevation but not the distance, lands in no-man's land between mid on and mid off.
back of a length on leg stump and angling in towards middle, defended off the back foot back to the bowler
short on the off, chopped down wide of third man for a couple. Rauf runs well to his right to pull off a good diving stop.
back of a length on middle stump, pushed wide of short extra-cover
slower ball bowled from over the wicket outside off, guided straight to point
bowled on a good length on the off, played wide of point for a single
Poor ball! pitched on a good length on leg stump, Chattergoon flicks it to the fine leg boundary.
on a good length on the off, Chattergoon gets onto the back foot and pierces the gap between point and cover for his second consecutive boundary!! Third man had no chance there, that was well timed
pitched on a full length on leg stump and moving in a shade towards middle, defended watchfully on the front foot back to the bowler
back of a length on leg stump, worked away wide of mid on for a single
full on middle and off, pushed wide of mid off for a single
back of a length on middle and leg, worked away towards square leg for an easy single
short of a length on middle, mistimes a pull to mid on
back of a length on leg stump, no movement, worked away to fine leg for a single
full outside off stump, driven powerfully to mid off, can't get it past him, Gayle will feel a touch disappointed there
slower ball bowled from round the wicket on middle and off, Gayle watches it onto his bat and defends it on the off side
short of a length outside off, cut away off the back foot to the point boundary
full on middle and leg, clipped away uppishly towards deep mid wicket
bowled on a good length on the off, Gayle opens the face and guides to point

dropped That was pitched short on middle and leg, Gayle took a couple of steps forward and pulled it uppishly straight back past the bowler, who gets a finger to it but is not able to prevent a boundary.
full on middle and leg, Gayle stays in the crease, picks the length up, and deposits it over the long on boundary for a massive six
full outside leg stump, worked away towards fine leg.
short of a length on middle, Chattergoon oulls it over square leg, deep mid wicket runs to his right and keeps the batsmen down to two
bowled back of a length on middle and off, played to backward point
tossed up outside off and spinning away from the left hander, pushed wide of mid off for a single
flighted on leg stump and spun in towards middle, Chattergoon tries to sweep it fine, gets an under-edge onto his pads
pitches on a good length on middle, defended on the off side
tossed up, pitched on a good length on leg stump, worked away towards square leg for a single
short of a good length outside off, guided to short third-man
flatter, pitches back of a length on leg stump, pushed wide of mid wicket for a single
flat and quick on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
that was an off-break, pitched short outside leg and spun in towards middle, whipped away wide of deep mid wicket for a couple
pitched fuller on leg stump and spinning towards middle, defended watchfully
finally a conventional leg-break, tossed up on the off stump, pushed to extra cover
big one!!! tossed up, pitches on a full length on middle and off, a length ball that, Gayle gets under it and deposits it over the deep mid wicket boundary for a huge six
pitched on a good length outside leg, swept to short fine leg
flighted outside off, defended on the off side
gave it some more air this time, pitches full outside leg, swept to fine leg

flatter and slightly quicker through the air this time, pitched on a good length outside off, Chattergoon comes down the track and tries to loft it over mid on, does not time it well enough, the ball lobs up in the air and Khurram Manzoor takes a few steps back and takes a well judged catch.
pitched outside leg, worked away to mid wicket
tossed up outside off, pushed to point
short and wide, Sarwan latches onto it, cuts it between point and cover, and Misbah-ul-Haq chases well but fails to prevent a boundary. Sarwan is off
tossed up outside off, Gayle pushes it straight to extra cover
on a good length outside off, Gayle tries to defend on the front foot, gets an inside edge, almost drags it onto the stumps
fuller on the pads, flicked away towards deep square leg
short of a good length on leg stump and spinning towards middle, Sarwan thinks of working it away on the leg side, but ultimately pushes it back uppishly towards the bowler
short of a good length on middle, pushed to mid wicket
short outside the off, punched wide of deep extra cover for a couple
flighted outside leg stump, played to short fine leg
shorter on the off, dropped on the off side for a quick single
tossed up outside off, Sarwan gets outside the line and tries to work it towards mid wicket, is hit on the pads
tossed up outside off yet again, played wide of mid wicket for a run
wide outside off, left alone
single towards mid wicket
short of a length on middle and leg, shipped to deep mid wicket
full on the off, driven down the ground to long on
short of a length outside off, played to extra cover
flighted on the off, driven to long off
short of a length outside off, driven on the back foot to long off
short and wide, cut away to deep point for a single
on a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot back to the bowler
tossed up on off, worked away to mid wicket
flighted on middle and leg, swept to fine-leg
tossed up outside leg, spinning in towards middle, Gayle defends on the front foot
pitches on a good length on the off and spinning away, Gayle gets on the back foot and drives it to long off
on a good length outside off and spinning in, pushed wide of mid wicket for a single
tossed up on middle, Sarwan makes room, takes it on the half volley and lofts it between long off and deep extra cover for a boundary
short of a good length outside off, cut away wide of point for a single
pitched on a good length on leg stump, defended back to the bowler
flighted outside off, driven to extra cover
tossed up on middle and leg, driven down the ground for a single towards long on
on a good length on middle and leg, turned away wide of short fine leg for a single
doosra!! Pitched on the off and spun away from the right hander, chopped away wide of point for a single
tossed up on the off and spinning away, left alone
pitches on a good length on leg and spinning towards middle, played back to the bowler
tossed up on middle and off, pushed to extra cover
flighted on the off yet again, driven down the ground to long off for a single
flatter, quicker through the air, pitches on a full length outside off, driven to long off
on a good length on leg, played back to the bowler
tossed up outside off, pitches short of a good length and tries to square cut it on the front foot, misses
flighted outside off, driven straight to extra cover
on a good length on middle and leg, turned away towards square leg
flighted outside off, pushed to long off
short of a length on middle and leg, whipped away to deep square leg
full toss on off stump, pushed to long on
tossed up, pitches on a good length, Gayle works it away to deep square leg
short outside off, cut away wide of deep point for a couple
flighted outside off, Sarwan gets outside the line and turns it wide of short fine leg for a quick single
flat and quick, pitches full on middle stump, that was an arm ball, Gayle amost yorks himself and digs the ball out back to the bowler
short of a good length outside leg and spinning in, driven to deep mid wicket
flighted outside off, driven to long off
flighted outside off, too wide, Sarwan reaches for it and pushes it to deep extra cover
pushed to point
low full toss on leg stump, driven to long on
short outside off, punched off the  back foot to deep cover
flighted outside off, driven to long off. Gayle on 99!!
century!!! flat and quick on leg stump, flicked wide of short fine leg for a single. 100 off just 90 balls
short and wide, punched to deep cover off the back foot
tossed up outside off, pushed wide of point
short outside off, Sarwan keeps the deep cover fielder busy again
short outside leg, worked away to deep mid wicket
tossed up, short of a length outside off, Sarwan tries to cut that wide of point, misses
tossed up outside off, defended
bowled flatter, on a good length on the off, dropped short of the cover fielder for a single
short outside off, pushed to cover off the back foot for a quick single
flighted on leg stump, flicked towards deep square leg
an off break, bowled short on middle stump, pushed back to the bowler
short outside off, pushed back to the bowler
good length on off and middle, swept in front of deep mid wicket for a boundary.
short outside off, tries to guide to third man, misses
flat and quick outside off, pushed to extra cover
on a good length on middle and leg, pushed wide of Malik, but no single taken
on a good length outside off, worked away wide of mid wicket
wide outside off, left alone, given a wide
short outside off, cut away behind point, Fawad Lam rockets in a good throw from the deep towards the non-strikers end, Afridi takes down the stumps but Gayle is comfortably back for the second
short outside off, too close to cut, Sarwan tries to play it behind point, misses
pushed to sweeper cover
flighted on middle and leg, worked away to deep mid wicket
short on leg stump, pulled away wide of long on, but a diving stop prevents a boundary. Two taken
driven to long on
worked away behind square leg
cut away to deep point
tossed up outside off, defended on the front foot
short outside off, slapped off the back foot straight to mid off
pitches short of a good length on the off and angling in, tries to whip it towards square leg, hit on the thighs

dropped, he puts down a dolly!!! That pitched short of a good length on middle, Gayle tries to work that one away towards mid wicket, gets the leading edge back to the bowler, Gul makes an absolute mess of it
pitched short of a good length on middle and off, Gayle makes room and swats that one powerfully past the bowler, deflects off Gul's foot to the long off boundary.
bouncer!! Gayle ducks

gone!!! That dropped chance did not prove costly. That was fuller on middle and leg, Gayle gets on the back foot and clips it uppishly straight to mid wicket, where Shahid Afridi takes a straightforward catch. Gayle timed that one very well, but did not get the elevation. He walks back for a superb 113!!
tossed up outside the off, Saran gets on the front foot and pushes it wide of point for a single
tossed up on middle and off, defended
flighted outside leg stump, swept wide of short-fine leg for a couple
tossed up on middle and off, defended
flighted outside leg, flicked straight to square leg
on a good length on leg stump, pushed back to the bowler
short outside off, Sarwan makes a bit of room and cuts it wide of third man for a boundary
bouncer, too high, given a wide
beaten!! that pitched on a good length on the off stump and moved away, Sarwan tries to push it towards the covers off the back foot, misses
short of a length outside off, pushed to cover
short outside off yet again, Gul pitching too short here, cut away powerfully between cover and point for a boundary. Sarwan brings up his fifty!!
pitched on a good length on middle, Sarwan drops it on the off side, thinks of a single, but it isn't there.
full outside off, Sarwan gives himself some room and drives it beautifully between long off and deep extra cover, three taken
flighted outside leg stump, turned away to short fine leg
short of a good length on middle and leg, flicked to short-fine yet again

given out caught-behind!!! That was flat and quick outside leg stump, Sarwan tries to work that one in the direction of short-fine leg yet again, gets the thinnest of edge down the leg side, and Akmal moves to his left to take a good catch. An unfortunate way to get out.
short of a good length on the off, pushed back uppishly wide of Shahid Afridi for a single towards long on
that was tossed up, pitched on a good length on the off and spinning away from the left hander, a googly,is struck on the pads on the back foot, but that was missing off
short outside off, punched to sweeper cover
short outside off, Chanderpaul chops it wide of point for a couple
short on middle and off, pulled away wide of deep mid wicket but a diving stop prevents a boundary and restricts the batsmen down to a couple
short of a length on the off, pulled in front of the wicket, down to long on
short of a good length outside off, dropped on the off side for a quick single
on a good length outside off, turned wide of mid wicket for a single
on a good length outside off, defended to extra cover
tossed up outside leg, turned to deep square leg
flatter on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
tossed up on the off yet again, comes forward to defend
short of a good length outside off, guided to point
dropped, that was short of a good length outside off, Marshall gets onto the back foot to punch it wide of the covers, gets an outside edge and Akmal spills a regulation chance!!
tossed up outside off, defended
short of a good length outside off, Chanderpaul tries to guide that one down to third man, gets an under-edge on the bounce to the keeper
fuller on the pads this time, driven to a widish long on for a couple
short outside the off, Chanderpaul cuts that one away wide of third man for a boundary. Wrong line!!
on a good length on the off stump, pushed to the covers
on a good length on the off, pushed towards cover for a single
on a good length outside off, guided down to third-man for a single

starts with a full toss on middle stump, Marshall swings that one over deep mid wicket for boundary. The umpire signalled a six initially but replays indicated that the ball fell just short of the ropes
full on the leg stump, driven powerfully wide of long on for another boundary
three in a row!!1 flat outside off, Marshall gets on the back foot and swats that wide of extra cover and long on for a boundary!! Alam is bleeding runs here
tossed up on middle and leg, lofted over the bowlers end and on the bounce to long on for a single
flighted outside off stump, driven to long on for a single
pitched on middle and leg, tries to work that one away on the leg side, gets a leading edge towards extra cover
short on middle and leg, Marshall comes down the track to pull it over mid wicket, misses. Rauf saw him come down the track and pitched it short
short of a length outside off, swatted down the ground to long off
short again on middle stump, Marshall pulls this one away wide of long on for a boundary. That was hit powerfully!
low full toss on off stump, slower ball that one, played on the off side, no run taken
fuller on the off stump, driven uppishly to long on
short of a good length outside off, pushed straight to extra cover
bowled full on off and middle, driven straight to mid wicket
short of a good length outside off, swung away wide of long on for a couple
bowled 'im!! That was a slower ball outside off, Marshall makes room and tries to pull that one over mid wicket, gets an inside edge onto the stumps. Important wicket that!!
full outside off, opens the face and guides that one to deep point
on a good length outside off, Chanderpaul looks to work that one away on the leg side, misses and the ball gets to the keeper on the bounce
slower ball on leg stump, played back to the bowler
beaten!! pitched short of a good length on the off and moving away, looks to run that one down to third man, misses
short of a good length outside off, gets on the back foot and punches that one down to long on
short of a good length outside off, Chanderpaul runs that one down well wide of a squarish third man for a welcome boundary!!
short of a length on the off, looks to pull that wide of mid wicket, mistimes it back to the bowler
full outside leg and coming in just a touch, looks to drive that one towards mid wicket, is struck on the pads
low full toss on the off stump, driven to long off
wide down the leg side
on a good length outside off, dropped on the off side for a quick single
short of a good length outside off, guided down to third man for a single

on a good length on the off stump, Chanderpaul drops it on the off side  and runs down the wicket to steal a single, Tanvir, however, gets to the ball quickly and flips it back towards the stumps but misses them by a whisker. Chanderpaul would have been out had that hit
what a shot!! that pitched full outside off, Chanderpaul gets down on one knee and paddles it over the fine leg boundary.
short outside off, too high, given a wide
short of a length on middle and leg, played behind square leg for a single
yorker on middle and leg bowled from round the wicket, Baugh somehow manages to get the bat down in time and dig it out to long on
slower ball bowled full outside off, sliced away to deep point
on a good length on middle and leg, walks across to work it towards square leg, gets a thick outside edge to point
bouncer on middle, Baugh looks to pull, misses

gone!! that was bowled full on middle and leg, Baugh looks to turn that towards square leg, gets the leading edge and Shoaib Malik who's standing at the edge of the circle at mid wicket takes a good catch stretching to his left
full outside leg, almost yorker length, Chanderpaul walks across to lay it towards square leg, is struck on the pads, scrambles a leg bye
shot!! That was pitched full outside off, Nash plays a text-book drive wide of mid off for a boundary.
full on middle and leg, Chanderpaul comes down the track and lofts it between long on and deep mid wicket for a four!!
slower ball outside off, bowled full, Chanderpaul falis to pick and goes through with his attempted loft over mid off, the ball lobs up in the air and Salman Butt takes an easy catch
Yorker on middle and off, dug out back to the bowler
slower ball outside off yet again, played to point who prevents a single
short outside off, makes room and upper cuts that one down to third man for a single
low full toss on leg stump from round the wicket, turned to deep square leg
on a good length on middle and leg, dropped on the on-side for a quick single
slower ball on middle, pushed back uppishly wide of the bowler for a single
bouncer on leg stump, looks to pull that one away, misses
short on the middle yet again, looks to swing it away in the direction of square leg, fails to connect yet again
full toss outside off, driven to long off for a single
full outside off, makes room and drives it down the ground to long off

slower ball outside off, bowled full, guided down to third man, Nash tries to scramble back for the second, Gul rockets in a good throw and Akmal takes off the bails. The appeal is referred but Nash, who dives full length, is safe
that was pitched on a good length on off and middle, Nash walks across and tries to work it wide of the short-fine leg fielder, misses, is struck on the pads, and the batsmen scramble a leg bye

bowled 'im!!! That was pitched full on a good length on middle bowled from round the wicket, a slower ball, Taylor fails to pick it and goes for a wild swing over mid wicket, misses it completely and the middle stump is out of the ground!!
bowled im!!, he's on a hat-trick!! the middle stump takes a beating once again!! That was full, Darren Powell tries to drive it towards long off, misses, and is comprehensively bowled
that was full and wide outside off, the batsman reaches for it, misses
run out full and wide outside off, tries to reach for it, misses. The batsmen try to scramble a quick single but Akmal throws down the stumps to find Nash short of his ground.

inn2.comm: short of a good length on leg stump, pushed to mid wicket
short and wide outside off, moved away even further, rightly given a wide
short of a good length on middle and off, defended off the back foot to point
fuller, on a good length outside the off and angling away, prods at it, and is beaten
bowled quick, lands short of a good length on leg stump, dropped on the on-side
down the leg side this time, pitches on a good length, Butt tries to glance that one down fine, is hit on the pads, and gets a leg bye
an attempted bouncer, goes down the leg side

beaten!! That pitched on a good length outside off and moved away from the right hander, Khurram Manzoor was caught in two minds there, pushed at it initially but the ball evaded his bat at just the last moment
on a good length outside off, moving away, Butt leaves it alone
short of a good length on the leg stump, turned to square leg
short outside the off, Butt tries to cut that one uppishly over point, misses
short of a length on middle and off, played down to third man for a single
on a good length outside off and moving away, left alone
on a good length on the off, moving away, defended watchfully on the off side
back of a length on middle, defended off the back foot
bowled full on leg stump, Butt gets an inside edge onto right foot for a single towards square leg. That was quick. Had it pitched on middle, Butt may well have been in trouble
on a good length on leg stump, turned away to fine leg
on a good length outside off, defended back to the bowler on the front foot
on a good length outside off, held its line this time, Butt pushes at it, misses, and is beaten. Excellent carry to the keeper there!
a bouncer bowled on the off, Butt leaves that one alone
short of a good length on the off, defended on the back foot. Taylor bowling at a good pace here
short of a length outside off, guided to third man for a single
back of a length on leg stump, worked away to square leg
that was quick, hit the pitch hard, bowled short of a good length on middle and leg, Butt rocks back on the back foot and defends
excellent bouncer!! pitched short on middle, Butt evades it just in time. That had him in a spot of bother!! Good testing bowling here by Taylor
short of a good length outside off, played to point

down the leg side!! pitched short of a length on leg, Khurram tries to work it away fine, didn't touch anything on its way to the fine-leg boundary. But the umpire thinks it flicked his pads, gives it leg byes
short and wide, Khurram gets onto the front foot and bisects the gap between cover and point for his first boundary
on a good length outside off, defended
down the leg side yet again, pitches on a good length on middle and leg, Khurram moves across and gets a faint tickle to the fine-leg boundary
short and wide outside off, moving away even further, left alone, given a wide
poor bowling!! short and wide yet again, Manzoor reaches for it and cuts it over the point fielder. Third man runs to his right and pushes the ball back with his foot
full and wide, swinging away, went for an expansive drive, misses
on a good length outside off, steered to third man for a single
wide down the leg side
short on the off, pulled away over mid wicket, Chanderpaul chases and hauls it back to keep the batsmen down to a couple
full on the pads, worked wide of mid wicket for a single, there was an easy two there but Butt was ball-watching
slower ball pitches on the off and moves away from the left hander, Butt pushes at it, fails to read it, misses, and goes through to the keeper
slower ball on leg stump and moving towards middle, pushed to extra cover
short on the off, a bouncer, Butt leaves it alone
short on middle and leg, whipped off the hips towards fine-leg
short outside off, Butt cuts it uppishly to third man. The ball gets to him on the bounce
full outside the off, moving away, left alone
angling in, bowled from wide of the crease, pitches on a good length outside off, left alone
short of a good length outside off, defended awkwardly onto the off side
on a good length on middle and leg, pushed to mid on for a quick single
short and wide outside off, moving away, tries to cut it powerfully over point, misses
back of a length on odd, defended watchfully on the off side
short of a length outside off, kept low this time, Manzoor tries to cut it towards third man, but could not get his bat down in time
drifting on the pads, flicked away to fine leg
bouncer on middle, Butt mistimes a pull wide of square leg for a single
short outside off, chopped to point
fuller in length outside off, pushed to cover
full on middle and leg, almost yorker length, flicked to square leg, a freehit to come as it was a front-foot no-ball
full on middle and off, bowled from wide of the crease, struck down the ground to long off
short of a length on middle and swinging away, Butt goes for an ambitious pull over square leg, misses
full outside leg, slower ball, Butt tries to flick it to square leg, misses, and is struck on the pads. He's struggling here!!
full outside off, held its line, Butt tries to drive that in the direction of mid off, misses. There is a noise, but the umpire turns the appeal down. Did the bat hit the ground there?
on a good length on middle and off, pushed to mid off for a quick single
short of a good length outside off, punched off the back foot straight to short extra-cover
short and wide, a gift, Butt creams that over short extra cover for a boundary.
on a good length outside off, moving away, left alone
back of a length on the off stump, defended on the on-side
full outside the off, driven straight to mid off
on a good length on middle and leg, flicked to square leg
bowled on a full length outside off, left alone
short of a good length outside off, punched to extra cover
back of a length on middle and off, worked away towards square leg
full outside the off, Butt drives it down the ground past the bowler, Chanderpaul and Sarwan chase the ball, the former dives full length to pull the ball back, and the batsmen run three
on a good length outside off, left alone
back of a length on the off, pushed to mid on off the back foot
short and wide outside off, Butt punches that one towards extra cover where Xavier Marshall fields well
back of a length on middle, Butt comes down and pulls it straight to mid wicket

dropped, short of a length on middle, Butt goes for a pull over mid wicket, mistimes it, Jerome Taylor runs to his left but sees Miller charging down from the other direction, he pulls out at the last moment and the ball drops between them. Butt gets a life, thanks to some atrocious fielding!
driven to extra cover, full outside off
defended on the off side
on a good length outside off, defended towards extra cover
on a good length on middle and leg, moving away from the left hander, Butt makes room to play it on the off side, misses, and the ball goes over the stumps to the keeper
full on the off stump, driven down the ground wide of mid off, Sarwan chases the ball down and keeps the batsmen to two
short on the off, chopped down to point
short outside off, Butt tries to pull it towards mid wicket, gets an inside edge that drops just wide of the off stump. Butt continues to live dangerously!!
short outside off, punched to deep cover for a single
short outside off, Manzoor looks to cut, gets a thick outside edge to the third man boundary!! fifty up for Pakistan!!
on a good length on the off, flew off the pitch to the keeper who collects it above his head
on a full length on the leg stump, Butt tries to work that one fine, misses yet again and is struck on the pads
beaten!!! back of a length on the off and swinging in, Butt tries to push it square, misses
on a good length outside off, worked away from outside the off towards square leg for a single
back of a length outside off, cut away to third man
back of a length on middle, Butt gets on the back foot and whips it uppishly wide of square leg for a boundary
back of a length outside off, pulled away to the deep mid wicket boundary
full toss outside off, driven to mid off, there was a single there, but Butt sends him back. He's ball watching again.
short of a good length outside off, guided to third man for a single
on a good length on the off, defended straight to extra cover
full on the off, Butt drops it down short of extra cover for a quick single. Had that fielder hit the stumps direct, Butt would have been well short of his ground. His luck continues.
a good bouncer on middle, Manzoor ducks under it just in time

bowled 'im!! That was pitched back of a length on middle and off, Butt tries to run it down to third man, gets an inside edge onto the stumps. That was inevitable. He ended up staying there longer than he should have., The Windies finally make a breakthrough. Butt walks back for an unconvincing 24. Baker gets his first ODI wicket.
on a good length on the off stump, pushed to mid off for a quick single
bouncer over middle, left alone
back of a length outside off, Manzoor misses out. He tries to cut that one over point but fails to connect.
beaten! That was pitched on a good length on off and angling away, Manzoor looks to open the face, misses
bowled full outside off, Manzoor drives that one wide of mid off for a couple
tossed up outside the off, dropped on the off side for a quick single
flighted on middle and off, driven down the ground to long on for a single
full on middle and leg, driven to long on
on a good length on middle and leg, played wide of mid wicket
good length on middle and leg, flatter, pushed to long on
tossed up on middle and off, defended on the leg side
back of a length outside off, cut away to point, where the fielder fumbles and allows a single
short outside off, pushed to backward point
fuller outside off, pushed wide of point for a quick single
short of a length on middle, pulled to deep square leg
a well bowled bouncer! Manzoor ducks under it
on a good length on the off, cut down to third man
on a good length outside off, played down to short third-man
flighted on middle and off, driven down to long on
full on middle and leg, pushed to long on yet again
on a good length outside off, played wide of point for a quick single
short of a good length on middle and spinning towards leg, pushed straight to mid wicket
short of a good length on middle and leg, worked away to short fine-leg. The batsmen scramble a quick single but a direct hit would have had Younis Khan in trouble
short outside the off, played down to short-third man
short outside off yet again from the left-arm spinner bowling from round the wicket, cut away to deep point
tossed up on middle and leg, defended on the on-side
on a good length on leg stump, worked down wide of short-fine leg for a couple
back of a length on leg stump, driven off the back foot to long on
tossed up outside off, driven to long off
short of a good length outside off, played to third man
full outside off, steered to third man
short of a good length outside off, cut away to deep point
bowled on a full length on middle and off, driven to long off
on a good length outside off, chopped onto the off side
dropped,short of a good length outside off, Younis tries to cut that towards point, gets an under-edge that the keeper puts down
tossed up outside off, dropped onto the off side for a single
on a good length outside off, pushed towards cover, calls for a single, is sent back
on a good length on middle and leg, played straight to mid wicket
short of a good length outside off, pushed wide of cover for a quick single
pushed to mid wicket
played straight to short-extra cover, no run
back of a length on leg stump, flicked away wide of deep square leg for a couple
good length on leg stump and moving towards middle and off, defended back to the bowler
full outside off, run down to third man, fifty for Khurram Manzoor! Good, solid knock.
full outside off, Younis cashes in, drives that one beautifully wide of s diving short extra-cover for a boundary
full length on leg stump, Younis glances that one down to the fine-leg boundary. Pakistan on the move here.
short and wide, cut away straight to point. Younis will feel he missed out there.
tossed up on middle and off, turned away wide of short fine-leg for a single
flighted outside off, driven down the ground to long off
flat and quick, short ball on leg stump, tries to pull it over mid wicket, is struck high on the thighs and gets a single towards short-third man
flighted outside off, driven back to the bowler
tossed up on the off stump, reverse-swept wide of the short third-man fielder for three
full toss on middle, driven back to the bowler where Miller dives to his right, but fumbles, and allows a single
short of a good length outside off, cut away to deep point
tossed up on middle and leg, pushed wide of mid wicket for a single. Fifty partnership comes up
good length outside off, pushed wide of cover for a single
tossed up on middle and leg, driven to long on for a single
flicked behind square leg
back of a length on middle, pushed off the back foot to long on
short of a good length on middle and off, pushed wide of the bowler towards long on for a single
flatter outside the off, bowled fuller, late cut wide of short third-man for a couple more
tossed up on middle and off, dropped on the off side for a quick single
flat on middle, pushed to the off side, short of point for another single
down the leg side
tossed up on the off, pitches on a full length, played to mid wicket
tossed up on the off stump, defended
bowled flat outside off, turned away wide of mid wicket for a single
quicker through the air on the off, pushed straight to extra cover
short and wide, cut away wide of deep point for a couple
back of a length outside off, guided wide of short-third man for a single
back of a length on middle and leg, pushed to mid wicket
full outside off, reverse-swept to short third-man
full in length outside off, guided to third man for a couple. Ramnaresh Sarwan could have been a little more agile there
back of a length outside off, defended to point
full toss on leg stump, tries to flick it away to square leg, gets an inside edge onto his pads
slower ball bowled back of a length outside off, played down to third man
bowled from behind the wicket, slower ball on middle, almost yorker length, an effective delivery that the batsman just about manages to dig out
excellent bowling. Follows it up with a quicker ball bowled back of the length outside off, tries to cut, misses. Good variation in pace there.
short and wide, struck powerfully but straight to extra cover
on a good length on middle, swept to deep square leg
short on the off and spinning away, cut away uppishly behind point for a couple

short and wide once again, Manzoor plays that down to deep cover
back of a length on the off, defended off the back foot
short of a length on middle and leg, pulled wide of mid wicket for a single
full on middle and leg, worked away on the on-side for a single

on a good length on the off and angling away just a touch, Manzoor stands his ground and tries t0 open the face to run it to third man, gets a thick outside edge and Carlton Bough dives to his right to take a sharp catch. Taylor strikes! Manzoor departs for a well made 69
bowled from behind the wicket, slower ball outside off, pushed wide of mid wicket for a single
back of a length on leg stump, worked away towards square leg
good length on leg stump, whipped away wide of mid wicket for a single
plays a pre-meditated reverse-sweep wide of short third man for a single, the bowler saw him and pitched it short on middle
fuller on leg stump, played towards square leg
back of a length on middle, played between square leg and mid wicket for a single
back of a length on middle, Younis gets down on one knee and sweeps it powerfully to the deep square leg boundary
fuller outside the off, driven to long off
fuller outside the off, chopped to point where Gayle throws down the stumps at the non-strikers end. The batsmen get a single as the ball ricochets off the stumps towards mid wicket
on a good length outside off, guided wide of third man where some lethargic fielding allows the batsmen to come back for the second
full on the off, driven to long off

bowled 'im! that was an arm ball bowled full on middle and leg, Misbah gets down on one knee to reverse-sweep that one down towards third-man, misses it completely, and the off stump is out of the ground. Too much unconventional strokeplay in his brief innings
on a good length on middle and odd, pushed off the back foot to long on
back of a length on middle, turned towards square leg
short of a good length on the off, driven back to the bowler
on a good length on off, driven back uppishly wide of the bowler, just falls short of Miller there
back of a length on middle and leg, whipped wide of mid wicket for a single

fifty for Younis! worked that one away wide of short fine leg for a single

on a good length on leg stump, played straight to mid wicket
on a full length outside off, driven for a couple towards deep extra cover

pushed wide of mid wicket for a single
reverse swept wide of short third man for a quick single
swept straight to short fine leg
down the leg side
back of a length on leg stump, played straight to mid wicket off the back foot

on a good length on leg, clips the pads on the way to the keeper
full on middle and leg, driven to mid wicket for a single
short of a good length on middle and leg, clipped wide of mid wicket for a single

on a good length on middle and leg, Malik drives that one uppihsly wide of the bowler for a boundary. Long off ran well to his right and put in a valiant effort, but failed to prevent the ball from rolling over the boundary rope
pushed behind point for a single
on a good length outside off, that was really wide, Malik cashes in, he takes a couple of steps down the track and smashes that wide of extra cover for a boundary.
Another four! That was full and wide outside off, Malik walks across and steers that wide of a diving point for a boundary. Runs flowing for Pakistan now
back of a length on the off, driven on the up to deep extra cover
short on middle and leg pulled away to short-fine leg, the batsmen scramble a quick single
slower ball outside off, tries to cut, left alone to the keeper
slower ball outside off yet again, attempts a cut, the same result, misses, and goes through to the keeper
short of a length outside off, pulled away deep square leg
on a good length outside off, Malik shuffles towards the off, and pushes that one wide of mid wicket for a single
full outside the off, tries to drive, beaten
good bowling. good length on the off, played back to the bowler

on a good length outside off, Younis tries to loft that one over long on, got the elevation but not the distance, went really high, Chattergoon at mid off took a couple of steps back and took a well judged catch. He almost fumbled it on the first attempt, but kept his composure to pouch it cleanly in the end. Big Blow!
short outside off, chopped down tho third man for a single
short outside the off yet again, run down to third man
full ball on middle and leg, flicked away to deep square leg
that was pitched full outside the off, driven uppishly wide of mid off for a much needed boundary. good shot that, under difficult circumstances.
short outside the off, run down to third man for a single
slower ball down the leg side
slower ball outside off, driven straight to mid off
full toss on leg stump, flicked to deep square leg
back of a length on leg stump, tries to work it away fine, gets an inside edge onto his pads.
on a good length outside off, played uppishly wide of extra cover
short of a length on the off, Afridi mistimes a pull down the ground mid on
slower ball on the off, a length ball, Malik gets under it and strikes it powerfully over the bowlers head for a boundary. He's on 49 now
on a good length on middle and leg, worked away wide of mid wicket for a single. An excellent fifty from the Pakistan captain

what a catch!! Could that be the decisive blow!! short of a length on the off stump, Afridi pulled that one uppishly towards deep square leg, that was very well struck, but Chanderpaul runs across to his right and dives to his right just inches within the boundary ropes to take a magnificent catch! Afridi goes, and the match takes a new twist. We are heading for an exciting finish here.
dropped That was pitched outside off and was angling away just a touch, Malik gets a faint kick to Baugh, who drops it diving to his right.
on a good length outside the off, Malik tries to drive on the up, misses
short of a length outside off, cut away uppishly towards third man
slower ball outside off, played away to backward point
bouncer outside off, too high
bouncer, gets it right this time, Fawad ducks
driven to long off
short of a length outside off, pulled down to long on
on a good length outside off, stepped out and driven down the ground to long off
tries to sweep, misses and is rapped on the pads
short outside off, cut away wide of deep point for a couple
that was tossed up on leg stump, Alam makes room and lofts towards long on for a single
that was flat on middle and off, Malik charges down the track, takes it on the half volley and smashes it over the long on boundary for a much needed six
back of a length on the leg stump, worked away wide of a diving short fine-leg fielder, who gets his fingers to it, for a couple
slower ball on a good length on the off, pushed wide of the bowler. Long off runs in but fails to pick the ball up cleanly, the batsmen scramble two
full and wide outside off, steers it wide of point for a single
on a good length outside off, Malik plays it back to the bowler, who misfields and allows a single
slower ball outside leg, looks to swing it over mid wicket, mistimes it along the ground, quick single taken
back of a length outside off, guided to third man for a single
full on middle and leg, driven to long on
short and wide, Alam latches onto that one, cuts that uppishly over point to the boundary well wide of third man
on a good length outside off, played wide of extra cover for a single
short outside the off, run down to third man
slower ball outside the off and moving away even further, given a wide.
short on middle, pulled away wide of mid wicket for a single
short of a length on middle, Malik makes room and chops that one down to third man
low full toss on leg stump, chipped to long on

full toss wide of the off stump, was pretty high, gets an outside edge that Baugh fails to hold on to, a really difficult chance, and the batsmen take a single. Surprised that wasn't given a no-ball, was well above the waist
quick and flat down the leg side, Baugh collects well and takes off the bails. Malik is well in. An attempted legside stumping there, was worth a try, given a wide though
low full toss on leg stump, played away to deep mid wicket
full, yorker length outside off, has a wild swing at it , misses
full toss on middle and leg, pushed away to deep point.
low full toss on the leg stump, makes room and drives that one straight to mid wicket, gets a single for his troubles.

gone!! Malik goes!! What a wicket. That was bowled on a good length outside off, Malik tries to swing that one over mid wicket, but finds Shivnarine Chanderpaul stationed there exactly for that shot, right at the edge of the circle. Malik plays a brilliant hand, but did he make enough?
slower ball outside off, guided to third man
full, yorker length outside off, good ball, driven to mid off, single taken
slower ball on middle and off, swung away, mistimed rather, to mid wicket
good length on the leg stump, pushed to mid on

bowled from behind the wicket, that was a slower ball outside leg stump, Kamran Akmal picks it up and deposits it over the fine-leg boundary for a crucial six! What a shot. This match will be settled in the final over
full outside off stump, driven back to the bowler. Good ball
low full toss on leg stump, driven down the ground to long on
bowled off a no-ball!! What a mistake Gayle has committed!! He's overstepped and bowled the batsman off a good length ball on the off stump. free hit coming!!
fulltoss outside off stump, played uppishly to long on.
full outside off stump, Akmal tries to drive that one through the off side, that was bowled on a yorker length, Baugh takes off the bauls and appeals. The appeal is being referred. He's in.. Not out.
low fulltoss on the off yet again, comes down the track and drives it to deep extra cover. What an over this has been
low full toss outside off, the batsman has no chance to dispatch that one, excellent length, all he can do is push it to mid off
full outside the off, tries to strike that powerfully over long off, does not connect it well, lands to the fielder on the bounce
big one!! full outside off, a length ball that deserves the treatment, Akmal lofts that over long off for a big six!!
six six six. short of a good length outside off, Akmal makes room and slices that one over deep point for a massive six!! Pakistan are back in this!! What a match

on a good length on middle, Akmal swings it away wide of mid wicket where the fielder dives to pull off a good save. But an overthrow allows the batsmen another run, three taken in all. West Indies have thrown it away here!!
full on leg stump, Alam makes room and drives it wide of mid on for a single. Pakistan win!! What a match. 17 needed off the final over, and two big hits from Akmal swings it Pakstan's way.
